generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 4180 feet, Slide Mountain is a standout peak in New York. Known for its approachable and scenic terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Wittenberg-Cornell-Slide Loop**, a **14.0 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **Adirondack 46ers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **Wittenberg Mountain**, which is just 1.9 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.

data_sources.notes: Elevation (4,180 ft) from USGS benchmark - highest peak in the Catskill Mountains. Named after massive landslide. Trail distance from NYS DEC and Catskill 3500 Club guides. Part of Catskill High Peaks.
